That is true. That generation doesn't understand.

353
00:26:14.090 --> 00:26:17.350
- True. 
 - You're the worst.

354
00:26:17.350 --> 00:26:19.420
No!

355
00:26:19.420 --> 00:26:23.190
Maybe it's a problem to be hung up on marriage and having children.

356
00:26:24.240 --> 00:26:28.930
I'm tired... I'm so tired.

357
00:26:35.380 --> 00:26:37.780
Should I tell you something scary?

358
00:26:41.960 --> 00:26:44.090
I'm your future.

359
00:26:49.300 --> 00:26:52.880
- Why me? 
 - Why is she my future?

360
00:26:54.040 --> 00:26:57.110
You're in big trouble now.

361
00:26:57.700 --> 00:27:00.630
Let's see.

362
00:27:02.630 --> 00:27:04.510
<i>The new editor-in-chief isn't married, right?</i>

363
00:27:04.510 --> 00:27:09.070
<i>She says she can sympathize with new mothers but I can tell she's single.</i>

364
00:27:11.420 --> 00:27:13.990
<i>A single lady talking about childcare? What could she know?</i>

365
00:27:13.990 --> 00:27:16.450
<i>If you're single, can you really be a reporter on childcare?</i>

366
00:27:16.450 --> 00:27:21.330
<i>Women with children can't be reporters. They work overtime a lot and don't go home often.</i>

367
00:27:24.620 --> 00:27:29.640
