374
00:27:50.610 --> 00:27:56.070
<i>Even if the editor-in-chief position is vacant, it would be hard for you.</i>

375
00:27:56.070 --> 00:28:01.250
<i>You know, right? They don't let single women be editor-in-chief for "the baby."</i>

376
00:28:04.010 --> 00:28:07.500
<i>Do you think I'll never get married?</i>

377
00:28:08.480 --> 00:28:13.530
<i>- What? 
 - I want to have a child. If I meet someone, I'm going to hurry into it.</i>

378
00:28:14.830 --> 00:28:17.030
<i>When is that?</i>

379
00:28:18.450 --> 00:28:21.510
<i>Don't stay at an impossible childcare magazine.</i>

380
00:28:21.510 --> 00:28:25.530
<i>Go where an editor-in-chief spot is guaranteed and get settled.</i>

381
00:28:25.530 --> 00:28:29.450
<i>I'm saying this for your sake.</i>

382
00:28:43.320 --> 00:28:45.350
Hari doesn't come here often.

383
00:28:45.350 --> 00:28:48.360
There's no reason you'll run into her!

384
00:28:48.360 --> 00:28:50.480
Seriously...

385
00:28:50.480 --> 00:28:52.510
Do you have a place?

386
00:28:53.040 --> 00:28:57.100
I moved today. In Hangangdong near the park.

387
00:28:57.550 --> 00:28:59.310
Hangangdong...

388
00:28:59.310 --> 00:29:00.860
Park?

389
00:29:01.700 --> 00:29:03.480
Of all places...

390
00:29:03.840 --> 00:29:06.120
Hari's neighborhood.

391
00:29:12.770 --> 00:29:16.420
- Hello. 
 - Welcome!

392
00:29:17.180 --> 00:29:20.820
